2026-03-08T01:11:53.128332Z  INFO session_loop{thread_id=019ccaf6-2bf0-7691-a2ef-34dbb14d060b}:submission_dispatch{submission.id="019ccafe-4278-7c33-937f-79932b809abb"}:turn{otel.name="session_task.turn" thread.id=019ccaf6-2bf0-7691-a2ef-34dbb14d060b turn.id=019ccafe-4278-7c33-937f-79932b809abb model=gpt-5.4}: codex_core::stream_events_utils: ToolCall: exec_command {"cmd":"cat > docs/00-general-docs.md <<'EOF'\n# General Docs Index\n\nRead this file first. It is the index for the minimum documentation contract used by the `.codex` workflow.\n\n## Core Contracts\n- `docs/tech-stack.md` - Authoritative summary of the repository stack, tools, runtime assumptions, and phase-specific model guidance.\n- `docs/architecture.md` - Operating model for `.codex`, repository boundaries, phase flow, and enforcement layers.\n- `docs/commands.md` - Supported local commands, validation scripts, dry-run workflow, and observability conventions.\n\n## Security\n- `docs/security-publishing.md` - Safe repository publication policy, denylist, checks, CI enforcement, and incident response.\nEOF\n\ncat > docs/tech-stack.md <<'EOF'\n# Tech Stack\n\n## Repository Type\nThis repository is a `.codex` orchestration template, not an application service.\n\n## Primary Assets\n- Markdown documentation in `docs/`\n- Prompt entrypoints in `.codex/prompts/`\n- Policies in `.codex/policies/`\n- Role definitions in `.codex/roles/`\n- Reusable guidance in `.codex/knowledge/`\n- Validation scripts in `scripts/`\n- CI checks in `.github/workflows/`\n\n## Runtime\n- Codex local workspace execution\n- Git repository for branch-based feature work\n- Shell-based validation scripts\n\n## Model Guidance\n- Planning and design: higher reasoning, lower tool pressure\n- Implementation: balanced reasoning with explicit verification commands\n- Audit and review: higher skepticism and findings-first output\n- Shipping and PR: low creativity, strict procedural execution\n\n## Stack Profiles\nThis template is stack-agnostic by default.\nProject-specific frontend or backend rules only apply when `docs/architecture.md` declares that stack profile.\nEOF\n\ncat > docs/architecture.md <<'EOF'\n# Architecture\n\n## Purpose\nThis repository defines an agent operating model for Codex-driven development.\n\n## Layers\n1. `docs/` defines project facts and repository contracts.\n2. `.codex/policies/` defines stable invariants.\n3. `.codex/prompts/` provides thin phase entrypoints.\n4. `.codex/roles/` scopes responsibilities by role.\n5. `.codex/knowledge/` stores reusable heuristics and implementation standards.\n6. `scripts/` and `.github/workflows/` enforce key rules.\n\n## Phase Flow\n1. `think` - read-only investigation, design, and plan generation\n2. `forge` - implementation against an approved plan\n3. `test` - test strategy and verification loops\n4. `audit` - read-only health and security review\n5. `ship` / `pr` - manual delivery workflows\n\n## Stack Profile\nDefault profile: generic repository orchestration.\nOnly load framework-specific backend or frontend rules when the target repository actually contains that stack.\n\n## Enforcement Principle\nA documented rule without an executable check is advisory.\nCritical rules should be enforced through scripts, hooks, or CI.\nEOF\n\ncat > docs/commands.md <<'EOF'\n# Commands\n\n## Validation\n- `./scripts/repo-audit.sh` - verifies required docs, denylisted runtime artifacts, and referenced script paths\n- `./scripts/prepublish-check.sh` - publication safety gate; runs the repo audit and checks tracked files\n- `./scripts/validate-plan.sh <plan-dir>` - verifies required phase artifacts and unfinished tasks\n\n## Dry-Run Workflow\n1. Run `/think` to generate a plan in `.orchestrator/plans/`\n2. Review and edit the generated `plan.md` if needed\n3. Run `/forge execute` from a feature branch\n4. Run `/test` or local validation commands\n5. Run `/ship` or `/pr` manually\n\n## Operational Guidance\n- Use a feature branch for implementation work\n- Keep tasks atomic and verifiable\n- Update indexed docs in the same checkpoint as code changes\n- Prefer shell validation over narrative-only policy\n\n## Observability Conventions\nRecord these fields in implementation logs when possible:\n- task name\n- files changed\n- verify command\n- retry count\n- outcome\n- finished timestamp\nEOF\n\ncat > docs/security-publishing.md <<'EOF'\n# Security Publishing Guide\n\n## Goal\nPublish this workspace without leaking credentials, local state, logs, or planning artifacts.\n\n## Classification (Denylist/Allowlist)\nRun:\n\n```bash\n./scripts/repo-audit.sh\n```\n\nDefault denylist:\n- `.codex/auth.json`\n- `.codex/history.jsonl`\n- `.codex/log/`\n- `.codex/state_*.sqlite*`\n- `.codex/sessions/`\n- `.codex/tmp/`\n- `.codex/shell_snapshots/`\n- `.orchestrator/plans/`\n\n## Pre-Publish Checklist\n1. Ensure `.gitignore` contains required security patterns.\n2. Run `./scripts/prepublish-check.sh`.\n3. Confirm denylisted files are not tracked by git.\n4. Resolve scanner findings before any push.\n\n## Local Hook Setup\nUse the repository hooks in `.codex/hooks/` or wire the scripts into your preferred pre-commit tooling.\n\n## CI Enforcement\n- `.github/workflows/secrets-scan.yml` blocks merges when the publication checks fail.\n- `.github/workflows/contract-drift.yml` blocks merges when required docs or scripts are missing.\n\n## Incident Response\n1. Revoke or rotate leaked credentials immediately.\n2. Remove secrets from history with `git filter-repo` or equivalent.\n3. Re-run the publication checks until they pass.\n4. Document root cause and prevention updates.\nEOF\n\ncat > .codex/MANUAL.md <<'EOF'\n# Codex Orchestration Manual\n\nThis repository is a Codex-oriented orchestration template for docs-first planning, implementation, testing, auditing, and manual delivery.\n\n## Core Idea\n- `docs/` contains repository facts and required contracts.\n- `.codex/policies/` contains stable rules.\n- `.codex/prompts/` are phase entrypoints, not the source of truth.\n- `scripts/` and CI turn critical rules into executable checks.\n\n## Phase Entry Points\n- `/think` - read-only investigation, design, and planning\n- `/forge execute` - implement the latest approved plan on a feature branch\n- `/test` - run the testing workflow for a feature or module\n- `/audit` - produce a read-only health report\n- `/ship` / `/pr` - manual delivery only\n\n## Non-Negotiable Rules\n1. Read `docs/00-general-docs.md` first.\n2. Do not work directly on `main` for implementation tasks.\n3. Do not auto-commit or auto-push outside manual delivery prompts.\n4. Keep tasks atomic and verifiable.\n5. Update indexed docs when implementation changes repository behavior.\n\n## Execution Notes\n- The latest plan lives in `.orchestrator/plans/`.\n- `think` creates `investigation.md`, `design.md`, and `plan.md`.\n- `forge` creates `implementation.md` and advances tasks one by one.\n- If a rule is critical, back it with a script or CI check.\n\n## Stack Profiles\nThis template is generic by default.\nLoad framework-specific frontend or backend guidance only when the target repository actually uses that stack and the docs contract says so.\nEOF\n\ncat > .codex/policies/global.md <<'EOF'\n# Global Rules for Development\n\nThese rules define the canonical operating contract for this repository.\n\n## 1. Documentation Contract\n- `docs/` is the primary source of truth for project-specific facts.\n- Every task must start by reading `docs/00-general-docs.md` and following its links.\n- Required baseline docs are `docs/tech-stack.md`, `docs/architecture.md`, `docs/commands.md`, and `docs/security-publishing.md`.\n- If implementation changes behavior, update the relevant indexed docs in the same checkpoint.\n\n## 2. Planning and Execution\n- Create a timestamped directory in `.orchestrator/plans/` for every task-oriented workflow.\n- Follow the phase lifecycle: Investigation, Design, Plan, Implementation.\n- Record major decisions in plan artifacts.\n- Abort after 3 failed verification attempts on the same task.\n\n## 3. Git and Delivery\n- Use Conventional Commits for manual delivery.\n- Do not run `git commit` or `git push` automatically during planning or implementation prompts.\n- Only `/ship` and `/pr` may perform manual delivery steps after explicit user confirmation.\n- Implementation work should happen on a feature branch, not directly on `main`.\n\n## 4. Enforcement\n- Critical rules must be backed by scripts, hooks, or CI.\n- Do not use `git add -f` for ignored runtime or tool artifacts.\n- No hardcoded secrets. Use environment files or platform secret stores.\n\n## 5. Stack Discovery\n- Do not assume a specific framework stack.\n- Consult `docs/tech-stack.md` and `docs/architecture.md` before loading framework-specific guidance.\nEOF\n\ncat > .codex/policies/strict-boundaries.md <<'EOF'\n# Strict Domain Boundaries\n\n## Purpose\nPrevent context pollution and cross-domain edits without an explicit handoff.\n\n## Iron Rule\nAn agent should stay within the domain implied by the active task and stack profile.\nIf it must cross domains, it should do so deliberately and document why.\n\n## Default Generic Profiles\n### `@architect`\n- Domain: `docs/`, `.codex/`, repository-level architecture, delivery rules, and enforcement design.\n- Avoid: implementation details that belong to stack-specific application code.\n\n### `@doc-planner`\n- Domain: `.orchestrator/plans/`, `docs/`, repository workflow design, and execution logs.\n- Avoid: unrelated application refactors.\n\n### `@implementation`\n- Domain: only the files required by the active task and declared stack profile.\n- Avoid: broad repo-wide edits without plan coverage.\n\n## Optional Stack-Specific Overlays\nApply these only when the target repository declares the stack in `docs/architecture.md`.\n\n### Backend Overlay\n- Domain: server code, runtime config, persistence, and backend tests.\n- Avoid: frontend assets unless the task explicitly spans both sides.\n\n### Frontend Overlay\n- Domain: UI code, client state, styling, and frontend tests.\n- Avoid: backend code unless the task explicitly spans both sides.\n\n## Error Prevention\nIf a task requires files outside the active domain, document the handoff or expand the plan before editing.\nEOF\n\ncat > .codex/roles/backend.md <<'EOF'\n---\nname: backend\ndescription: Backend specialist for repositories that declare a backend stack profile.\n---\n\n# Backend Specialist\n\nUse this role only when the target repository contains backend code and the docs contract declares a backend stack.\n\n## Start Here\n- Read `docs/00-general-docs.md`\n- Read `docs/tech-stack.md`\n- Read `docs/architecture.md`\n- Then load the backend-specific docs referenced there\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Implement backend behavior defined by the plan\n- Keep business logic decoupled from delivery concerns\n- Validate inputs and preserve data integrity\n- Add or update tests for backend behavior\n\n## Guardrails\n- Do not assume Spring, Java, or any other framework unless the docs contract says so\n- Do not edit frontend-only files unless the task explicitly spans both domains\nEOF\n\ncat > .codex/roles/frontend.md <<'EOF'\n---\nname: frontend\ndescription: Frontend specialist for repositories that declare a frontend stack profile.\n---\n\n# Frontend Specialist\n\nUse this role only when the target repository contains frontend code and the docs contract declares a frontend stack.\n\n## Start Here\n- Read `docs/00-general-docs.md`\n- Read `docs/tech-stack.md`\n- Read `docs/architecture.md`\n- Then load the frontend-specific docs referenced there\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Implement UI behavior defined by the plan\n- Keep presentation and logic cleanly separated when complexity warrants it\n- Preserve accessibility, responsiveness, and user feedback\n- Add or update tests for frontend behavior\n\n## Guardrails\n- Do not assume React, Tailwind, or TypeScript unless the docs contract says so\n- Do not edit backend-only files unless the task explicitly spans both domains\nEOF\n\ncat > .codex/roles/architect.md <<'EOF'\n---\nname: architect\ndescription: Repository architect for docs contracts, system boundaries, APIs, and enforcement design.\n---\n\n# Repository Architect\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Define and maintain repository-level architecture\n- Keep docs contracts coherent and complete\n- Select patterns based on the actual stack declared in `docs/`\n- Review changes that affect boundaries, APIs, data contracts, or delivery rules\n\n## Working Rules\n- Read `docs/00-general-docs.md` first\n- Treat `docs/` as the authority for project facts\n- Prefer enforceable rules over narrative-only policy\nEOF\n\ncat > .codex/roles/doc-planner.md <<'EOF'\n---\nname: doc-planner\ndescription: Planning and documentation specialist for task breakdown, checkpoints, and docs synchronization.\n---\n\n# Documentation Planner\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Create and maintain plan artifacts in `.orchestrator/plans/`\n- Break work into atomic, verifiable tasks\n- Keep indexed docs synchronized with implementation changes\n- Maintain repository workflow clarity\n\n## Working Rules\n- Read `docs/00-general-docs.md` first\n- Use the docs index to find the exact files to update\n- Prefer simple, durable docs over speculative detail\nEOF\n\ncat > .codex/knowledge/parallel-orchestration/SKILL.md <<'EOF'\n---\nname: parallel-orchestration\ndescription: Multi-agent coordination pattern for Codex-style repository work. Use when a task needs separate passes for architecture, security, implementation, or review.\n---\n\n# Parallel Orchestration\n\n## Overview\nCoordinate specialized passes when one perspective is not enough.\nUse parallel or staged analysis only when the task benefits from separation of concerns.\n\n## Domain Teams\n| Team | Roles involved | Trigger |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| New Feature | `@architect` -> `@doc-planner` -> implementation role | New repository behavior |\n| Security Audit | `@architect` -> security-focused reviewer | Sensitive change or publication review |\n| Doc Polish | `@doc-planner` -> `@architect` | Documentation cleanup or contract drift |\n\n## Pattern\n1. Explorer maps the current state.\n2. Specialists review from their domain perspective.\n3. A final synthesis reconciles conflicts into one decision record or plan.\n\n## Rules\n- Keep handoffs explicit.\n- Keep outputs unified.\n- Do not duplicate context unless it changes the result.\nEOF\n\ncat > .codex/knowledge/subagent-driven-development/SKILL.md <<'EOF'\n---\nname: subagent-driven-development\ndescription: Use when executing implementation plans. Dispatches a fresh execution context per atomic task with review and verification.\n---\n\n# Subagent-Driven Development (SDD)\n\n## Loop\n1. Dispatch one fresh execution context for one task.\n2. Validate spec compliance.\n3. Validate quality, docs sync, and verification output.\n4. Record the result in `plan.md` and `implementation.md`.\n\n## Laws\n- One task per execution context.\n- Pass the exact task text, not just the file path.\n- Re-review fixes through the same review lens.\n- Include the verify command and outcome in the log.\nEOF\n","workdir":"/Users/lewis/1-Backup/0-devback/archive/codex_ai-agentic-sdd","yield_time_ms":1000,"max_output_tokens":6000} thread_id=019ccaf6-2bf0-7691-a2ef-34dbb14d060b
2026-03-08T01:13:00.518131Z  INFO session_loop{thread_id=019ccaf6-2bf0-7691-a2ef-34dbb14d060b}:submission_dispatch{submission.id="019ccafe-4278-7c33-937f-79932b809abb"}:turn{otel.name="session_task.turn" thread.id=019ccaf6-2bf0-7691-a2ef-34dbb14d060b turn.id=019ccafe-4278-7c33-937f-79932b809abb model=gpt-5.4}: codex_core::stream_events_utils: ToolCall: exec_command {"cmd":"cat > docs/00-general-docs.md <<'EOF'\n# General Docs Index\n\nRead this file first. It is the index for the minimum documentation contract used by the `.codex` workflow.\n\n## Core Contracts\n- `docs/tech-stack.md` - Authoritative summary of the repository stack, tools, runtime assumptions, and phase-specific model guidance.\n- `docs/architecture.md` - Operating model for `.codex`, repository boundaries, phase flow, and enforcement layers.\n- `docs/commands.md` - Supported local commands, validation scripts, dry-run workflow, and observability conventions.\n\n## Security\n- `docs/security-publishing.md` - Safe repository publication policy, denylist, checks, CI enforcement, and incident response.\nEOF\n\ncat > docs/tech-stack.md <<'EOF'\n# Tech Stack\n\n## Repository Type\nThis repository is a `.codex` orchestration template, not an application service.\n\n## Primary Assets\n- Markdown documentation in `docs/`\n- Prompt entrypoints in `.codex/prompts/`\n- Policies in `.codex/policies/`\n- Role definitions in `.codex/roles/`\n- Reusable guidance in `.codex/knowledge/`\n- Validation scripts in `scripts/`\n- CI checks in `.github/workflows/`\n\n## Runtime\n- Codex local workspace execution\n- Git repository for branch-based feature work\n- Shell-based validation scripts\n\n## Model Guidance\n- Planning and design: higher reasoning, lower tool pressure\n- Implementation: balanced reasoning with explicit verification commands\n- Audit and review: higher skepticism and findings-first output\n- Shipping and PR: low creativity, strict procedural execution\n\n## Stack Profiles\nThis template is stack-agnostic by default.\nProject-specific frontend or backend rules only apply when `docs/architecture.md` declares that stack profile.\nEOF\n\ncat > docs/architecture.md <<'EOF'\n# Architecture\n\n## Purpose\nThis repository defines an agent operating model for Codex-driven development.\n\n## Layers\n1. `docs/` defines project facts and repository contracts.\n2. `.codex/policies/` defines stable invariants.\n3. `.codex/prompts/` provides thin phase entrypoints.\n4. `.codex/roles/` scopes responsibilities by role.\n5. `.codex/knowledge/` stores reusable heuristics and implementation standards.\n6. `scripts/` and `.github/workflows/` enforce key rules.\n\n## Phase Flow\n1. `think` - read-only investigation, design, and plan generation\n2. `forge` - implementation against an approved plan\n3. `test` - test strategy and verification loops\n4. `audit` - read-only health and security review\n5. `ship` / `pr` - manual delivery workflows\n\n## Stack Profile\nDefault profile: generic repository orchestration.\nOnly load framework-specific backend or frontend rules when the target repository actually contains that stack.\n\n## Enforcement Principle\nA documented rule without an executable check is advisory.\nCritical rules should be enforced through scripts, hooks, or CI.\nEOF\n\ncat > docs/commands.md <<'EOF'\n# Commands\n\n## Validation\n- `./scripts/repo-audit.sh` - verifies required docs, denylisted runtime artifacts, and referenced script paths\n- `./scripts/prepublish-check.sh` - publication safety gate; runs the repo audit and checks tracked files\n- `./scripts/validate-plan.sh <plan-dir>` - verifies required phase artifacts and unfinished tasks\n\n## Dry-Run Workflow\n1. Run `/think` to generate a plan in `.orchestrator/plans/`\n2. Review and edit the generated `plan.md` if needed\n3. Run `/forge execute` from a feature branch\n4. Run `/test` or local validation commands\n5. Run `/ship` or `/pr` manually\n\n## Operational Guidance\n- Use a feature branch for implementation work\n- Keep tasks atomic and verifiable\n- Update indexed docs in the same checkpoint as code changes\n- Prefer shell validation over narrative-only policy\n\n## Observability Conventions\nRecord these fields in implementation logs when possible:\n- task name\n- files changed\n- verify command\n- retry count\n- outcome\n- finished timestamp\nEOF\n\ncat > docs/security-publishing.md <<'EOF'\n# Security Publishing Guide\n\n## Goal\nPublish this workspace without leaking credentials, local state, logs, or planning artifacts.\n\n## Classification (Denylist/Allowlist)\nRun:\n\n```bash\n./scripts/repo-audit.sh\n```\n\nDefault denylist:\n- `.codex/auth.json`\n- `.codex/history.jsonl`\n- `.codex/log/`\n- `.codex/state_*.sqlite*`\n- `.codex/sessions/`\n- `.codex/tmp/`\n- `.codex/shell_snapshots/`\n- `.orchestrator/plans/`\n\n## Pre-Publish Checklist\n1. Ensure `.gitignore` contains required security patterns.\n2. Run `./scripts/prepublish-check.sh`.\n3. Confirm denylisted files are not tracked by git.\n4. Resolve scanner findings before any push.\n\n## Local Hook Setup\nUse the repository hooks in `.codex/hooks/` or wire the scripts into your preferred pre-commit tooling.\n\n## CI Enforcement\n- `.github/workflows/secrets-scan.yml` blocks merges when the publication checks fail.\n- `.github/workflows/contract-drift.yml` blocks merges when required docs or scripts are missing.\n\n## Incident Response\n1. Revoke or rotate leaked credentials immediately.\n2. Remove secrets from history with `git filter-repo` or equivalent.\n3. Re-run the publication checks until they pass.\n4. Document root cause and prevention updates.\nEOF\n\ncat > .codex/MANUAL.md <<'EOF'\n# Codex Orchestration Manual\n\nThis repository is a Codex-oriented orchestration template for docs-first planning, implementation, testing, auditing, and manual delivery.\n\n## Core Idea\n- `docs/` contains repository facts and required contracts.\n- `.codex/policies/` contains stable rules.\n- `.codex/prompts/` are phase entrypoints, not the source of truth.\n- `scripts/` and CI turn critical rules into executable checks.\n\n## Phase Entry Points\n- `/think` - read-only investigation, design, and planning\n- `/forge execute` - implement the latest approved plan on a feature branch\n- `/test` - run the testing workflow for a feature or module\n- `/audit` - produce a read-only health report\n- `/ship` / `/pr` - manual delivery only\n\n## Non-Negotiable Rules\n1. Read `docs/00-general-docs.md` first.\n2. Do not work directly on `main` for implementation tasks.\n3. Do not auto-commit or auto-push outside manual delivery prompts.\n4. Keep tasks atomic and verifiable.\n5. Update indexed docs when implementation changes repository behavior.\n\n## Execution Notes\n- The latest plan lives in `.orchestrator/plans/`.\n- `think` creates `investigation.md`, `design.md`, and `plan.md`.\n- `forge` creates `implementation.md` and advances tasks one by one.\n- If a rule is critical, back it with a script or CI check.\n\n## Stack Profiles\nThis template is generic by default.\nLoad framework-specific frontend or backend guidance only when the target repository actually uses that stack and the docs contract says so.\nEOF\n\ncat > .codex/policies/global.md <<'EOF'\n# Global Rules for Development\n\nThese rules define the canonical operating contract for this repository.\n\n## 1. Documentation Contract\n- `docs/` is the primary source of truth for project-specific facts.\n- Every task must start by reading `docs/00-general-docs.md` and following its links.\n- Required baseline docs are `docs/tech-stack.md`, `docs/architecture.md`, `docs/commands.md`, and `docs/security-publishing.md`.\n- If implementation changes behavior, update the relevant indexed docs in the same checkpoint.\n\n## 2. Planning and Execution\n- Create a timestamped directory in `.orchestrator/plans/` for every task-oriented workflow.\n- Follow the phase lifecycle: Investigation, Design, Plan, Implementation.\n- Record major decisions in plan artifacts.\n- Abort after 3 failed verification attempts on the same task.\n\n## 3. Git and Delivery\n- Use Conventional Commits for manual delivery.\n- Do not run `git commit` or `git push` automatically during planning or implementation prompts.\n- Only `/ship` and `/pr` may perform manual delivery steps after explicit user confirmation.\n- Implementation work should happen on a feature branch, not directly on `main`.\n\n## 4. Enforcement\n- Critical rules must be backed by scripts, hooks, or CI.\n- Do not use `git add -f` for ignored runtime or tool artifacts.\n- No hardcoded secrets. Use environment files or platform secret stores.\n\n## 5. Stack Discovery\n- Do not assume a specific framework stack.\n- Consult `docs/tech-stack.md` and `docs/architecture.md` before loading framework-specific guidance.\nEOF\n\ncat > .codex/policies/strict-boundaries.md <<'EOF'\n# Strict Domain Boundaries\n\n## Purpose\nPrevent context pollution and cross-domain edits without an explicit handoff.\n\n## Iron Rule\nAn agent should stay within the domain implied by the active task and stack profile.\nIf it must cross domains, it should do so deliberately and document why.\n\n## Default Generic Profiles\n### `@architect`\n- Domain: `docs/`, `.codex/`, repository-level architecture, delivery rules, and enforcement design.\n- Avoid: implementation details that belong to stack-specific application code.\n\n### `@doc-planner`\n- Domain: `.orchestrator/plans/`, `docs/`, repository workflow design, and execution logs.\n- Avoid: unrelated application refactors.\n\n### `@implementation`\n- Domain: only the files required by the active task and declared stack profile.\n- Avoid: broad repo-wide edits without plan coverage.\n\n## Optional Stack-Specific Overlays\nApply these only when the target repository declares the stack in `docs/architecture.md`.\n\n### Backend Overlay\n- Domain: server code, runtime config, persistence, and backend tests.\n- Avoid: frontend assets unless the task explicitly spans both sides.\n\n### Frontend Overlay\n- Domain: UI code, client state, styling, and frontend tests.\n- Avoid: backend code unless the task explicitly spans both sides.\n\n## Error Prevention\nIf a task requires files outside the active domain, document the handoff or expand the plan before editing.\nEOF\n\ncat > .codex/roles/backend.md <<'EOF'\n---\nname: backend\ndescription: Backend specialist for repositories that declare a backend stack profile.\n---\n\n# Backend Specialist\n\nUse this role only when the target repository contains backend code and the docs contract declares a backend stack.\n\n## Start Here\n- Read `docs/00-general-docs.md`\n- Read `docs/tech-stack.md`\n- Read `docs/architecture.md`\n- Then load the backend-specific docs referenced there\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Implement backend behavior defined by the plan\n- Keep business logic decoupled from delivery concerns\n- Validate inputs and preserve data integrity\n- Add or update tests for backend behavior\n\n## Guardrails\n- Do not assume Spring, Java, or any other framework unless the docs contract says so\n- Do not edit frontend-only files unless the task explicitly spans both domains\nEOF\n\ncat > .codex/roles/frontend.md <<'EOF'\n---\nname: frontend\ndescription: Frontend specialist for repositories that declare a frontend stack profile.\n---\n\n# Frontend Specialist\n\nUse this role only when the target repository contains frontend code and the docs contract declares a frontend stack.\n\n## Start Here\n- Read `docs/00-general-docs.md`\n- Read `docs/tech-stack.md`\n- Read `docs/architecture.md`\n- Then load the frontend-specific docs referenced there\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Implement UI behavior defined by the plan\n- Keep presentation and logic cleanly separated when complexity warrants it\n- Preserve accessibility, responsiveness, and user feedback\n- Add or update tests for frontend behavior\n\n## Guardrails\n- Do not assume React, Tailwind, or TypeScript unless the docs contract says so\n- Do not edit backend-only files unless the task explicitly spans both domains\nEOF\n\ncat > .codex/roles/architect.md <<'EOF'\n---\nname: architect\ndescription: Repository architect for docs contracts, system boundaries, APIs, and enforcement design.\n---\n\n# Repository Architect\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Define and maintain repository-level architecture\n- Keep docs contracts coherent and complete\n- Select patterns based on the actual stack declared in `docs/`\n- Review changes that affect boundaries, APIs, data contracts, or delivery rules\n\n## Working Rules\n- Read `docs/00-general-docs.md` first\n- Treat `docs/` as the authority for project facts\n- Prefer enforceable rules over narrative-only policy\nEOF\n\ncat > .codex/roles/doc-planner.md <<'EOF'\n---\nname: doc-planner\ndescription: Planning and documentation specialist for task breakdown, checkpoints, and docs synchronization.\n---\n\n# Documentation Planner\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Create and maintain plan artifacts in `.orchestrator/plans/`\n- Break work into atomic, verifiable tasks\n- Keep indexed docs synchronized with implementation changes\n- Maintain repository workflow clarity\n\n## Working Rules\n- Read `docs/00-general-docs.md` first\n- Use the docs index to find the exact files to update\n- Prefer simple, durable docs over speculative detail\nEOF\n\ncat > .codex/knowledge/parallel-orchestration/SKILL.md <<'EOF'\n---\nname: parallel-orchestration\ndescription: Multi-agent coordination pattern for Codex-style repository work. Use when a task needs separate passes for architecture, security, implementation, or review.\n---\n\n# Parallel Orchestration\n\n## Overview\nCoordinate specialized passes when one perspective is not enough.\nUse parallel or staged analysis only when the task benefits from separation of concerns.\n\n## Domain Teams\n| Team | Roles involved | Trigger |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| New Feature | `@architect` -> `@doc-planner` -> implementation role | New repository behavior |\n| Security Audit | `@architect` -> security-focused reviewer | Sensitive change or publication review |\n| Doc Polish | `@doc-planner` -> `@architect` | Documentation cleanup or contract drift |\n\n## Pattern\n1. Explorer maps the current state.\n2. Specialists review from their domain perspective.\n3. A final synthesis reconciles conflicts into one decision record or plan.\n\n## Rules\n- Keep handoffs explicit.\n- Keep outputs unified.\n- Do not duplicate context unless it changes the result.\nEOF\n\ncat > .codex/knowledge/subagent-driven-development/SKILL.md <<'EOF'\n---\nname: subagent-driven-development\ndescription: Use when executing implementation plans. Dispatches a fresh execution context per atomic task with review and verification.\n---\n\n# Subagent-Driven Development (SDD)\n\n## Loop\n1. Dispatch one fresh execution context for one task.\n2. Validate spec compliance.\n3. Validate quality, docs sync, and verification output.\n4. Record the result in `plan.md` and `implementation.md`.\n\n## Laws\n- One task per execution context.\n- Pass the exact task text, not just the file path.\n- Re-review fixes through the same review lens.\n- Include the verify command and outcome in the log.\nEOF\n","workdir":"/Users/lewis/1-Backup/0-devback/archive/codex_ai-agentic-sdd","yield_time_ms":1000,"max_output_tokens":4000,"sandbox_permissions":"require_escalated","justification":"Do you want me to update the repository’s .codex orchestration files so the workflow becomes consistent and Codex-native?","prefix_rule":["sh","-c"]} thread_id=019ccaf6-2bf0-7691-a2ef-34dbb14d060b
